reviews.text: I use this train to commute to Peterborough and back. When it works it runs nicely stress free travel. Sometimes there are no staff on in the morning so if you have a query that can be difficult. Although the star is for the staff member who is always very helpful to me. It is very disappointing there is no service on a Sunday which makes a weekend away nearly impossible or very expensive. On more than one occasion the train was cancelled and I was late. They have this delay repay and I contacted them. I buy a season ticket and they took over 7 weeks to reply and I got £2 compensation and a thank you for making them aware. I wish they would take comments on board so that we don't lose this service.

If I could find a symbol for 0 or at least 1/2 star rating I would.  Please can you tell me why when there is no other train due, last night the 18:36 train from Peterborough arrived in Spalding on the far platform making an excruciating climb up stairs and then down again before I could leave the station. I overheard the ticket collector saying to two policepersons that they no longer felt safe at the station because of the vandalism etc. HOW DO YOU THINK IT MAKES ME FEEL WHEN IT TAKES ME SO LONG TO GET AWAY FROM THE TRAIN!

Very nice and pleasant lady at the ticket office today 28/10/17She was very helpful and very cheerful,The station was nice apart from some young lads cycling up and down the platform,Would liked to have thanked the lady but didn't get her name

Very helpful clear and concise directions from ticket office staff. Nice  old fashion station with plenty of seating and most departures from platform 1. A hot drink vending machine for £1 which is quiet enjoyable and ticket machines that are working.
Lots of chewing gum on ground and very good train services
